straightforward /ˌstreɪtˈfɔːwəd/

1. ADJ If you describe something as straightforward , you approve of it because it is easy to do or understand. 容易的; 易懂的 [表赞许] 

例： Disposable diapers are fairly straightforward to put on. 一次性尿布非常容易穿。 

例： The question seemed straightforward enough. 这个问题看起来够容易的了。 

2. ADJ If you describe a person or their behaviour as straightforward , you approve of them because they are honest and direct, and do not try to hide their feelings. 坦率的 [表赞许] 

例： She is very blunt, very straightforward, and very honest. 她直言不讳，非常坦率，也非常诚实。

